                                                  ʿālam</title></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e2"><desc>Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly <locus target="#4v #5r #10r #10v" facs="009 014 015">folss. 4v, 5r, 10r, 10v, </locus>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#17v #92r #128v #136r" facs="022 096 133 140">17v, 92r, 128v, 136r, </locus>);
                      and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted to correct homoeoteleuton (<locus target="#136v" facs="141"> f. 136v, line 2</locus>;
                      <locus target="#140v" facs="145"> f. 140v, line 16</locus>);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#67r" facs="071">67r, </locus>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#6r #26r #28r #28v #66v" facs="010 030 032 033 071">6r, 26r, 28r, 28v, 66v</locus>)</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e3"><desc>This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample room for the width of most lines. On a few occasions, the line would have been too long and the scribe completes the line above or below the end of the line (e.g., <locus target="#3v #10v #12v" facs="008 015 017">fols. 3v, 10v, 12v</locus>).</desc></item>
